text: Gjøvik District Court () is a district court located in Gjøvik, Norway. The court was created on 1 January 2009, when Toten District Court and Hadeland og Land District Court was merged. It covers the municipalities of Gjøvik, Lunner, Gran, Søndre Land, Nordre Land, Østre Toten and Vestre Toten and is subordinate Eidsivating Court of Appeal.Gjøvik District Court ==References== == External links == *Official site Category:District courts of Norway Category:Organisations based in Gjøvik Category:2009 establishments in Norway Category:Courts and tribunals established in 2009
